metadata.name: Lagoon and Trifid
metadata.description:
The Lagoon and Trifid Nebulae.  These birthplaces of stars sit in the core of our Milky Way galaxy and are a Summer night treat to see.  This image was taken in a fairly dark sky (Bortle Class 4) in Virginia.  The pink and blue colors are the ionized Hydrogen and other gases that when condensed by the pull of gravity, will form new stars!  The nebulae sit in a large star field with millions of other stars pictured. 

Photographer: Jason Betzner

Collection: Deep Space

Edition: 1/1 NFT

Location: Williamsburg, Virginia, USA

Year Created: 2022

Genre: Astrophotography

Gear: Canon EOS 6D, Star Adventurer Pro tracker, William Optics Z61ii refractor.
